Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting impaired renal function with possible nephrotic features and glycosuria despite normal blood glucose and low HbA1c. These findings may indicate acute or chronic kidney disease, possibly with tubular dysfunction. Further nephrological evaluation and clinical correlation are recommended.
